{"key":"post-8626915","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8626915</id>\n<content>I used storebought bagged up cow manure for years on copelandia.&amp;nbsp; I never mixed with straw, but added a bit of verm and gypsum, and after adjusting moisture content, pasteurized in quart jars for an hour at 140F.&amp;nbsp; Using jars doesn't screw up your moisture content the way other methods do.&amp;nbsp;  Another common mistake is making thick substrates.&amp;nbsp; Pans prefer a thin substrate, around 1 1/2&quot;.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8627038</next>\n<prev>8626677</prev>\n<first>8626677</first>\n<last>8627980</last>\n<when>1215915957</when>\n<utime>07/13/08 05:25 AM</utime>\n</post>"}